content:
Use the Channel Menu component instead of the code snippet to add the menu and button to your Experience Cloud sites.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Channel Menu setup node is available in: Lightning Experience
Available in: Performance, Professional, Unlimited, and Essentials


USER PERMISSIONS NEEDED
To set up Channel Menu:	Customize Application AND Modify Metadata
To create and edit Salesforce Sites:	Customize Application
To edit public access settings for Salesforce Sites:	Manage Users

Enable the Guest Access to the Support API permission in Salesforce Admin Setup > Sites.
Click the Settings button in Experience Builder on the left side and select Security.
Change your Script Security Level to Allow Inline Scripts and Script Access to Allowlisted Third-party Hosts.
Click the Add Trusted Site button and add your Chat API Endpoint to your Trusted Sites for Scripts.
title: Service Cloud - Adding Channel Menu to Experience Cloud Sites
